Last year, the Durbanville man was taken into custody on child porn charges. Police believe that as many as 60 children may have fallen victim to the pastor. CAPE TOWN - A pastor has been arrested for a second time on charges relating to child porn. The youth pastor appeared in the Bellville Magistrate's court on Friday. The police's Andre Traut said: “He made a court appearance in Bellville on Friday morning and the case has been postponed until 27 March for a bail application.” Last year, the Durbanville man was taken into custody on child porn charges. Police believe that as many as 60 children may have fallen victim to the pastor.